        <h3>EHDSPatient → PatientEuCore</h3>
        <p class="lead">
      This page describes the mapping from the
            <a href="https://www.xt-ehr.eu/fhir/models/StructureDefinition/EHDSPatient">
                <strong>EHDSPatient</strong>
            </a>
      logical model to the <code>PatientEuCore</code> profile used in this Implementation Guide.
        </p>
        <p class="lead" style="font-size:0.9rem;">
            <strong>FHIR release note:</strong>
      The mapping is shown against the PatientEuCore profile in this guide. Where R4 vs R5 handling differs
      (e.g. structural changes in telecom or address), this is noted in the <em>Notes</em> column.
        </p>
        <div class="legend">
            <strong>Relationship legend</strong>
            <dl>
                <dt>equal</dt>
                <dd>Semantically equivalent.</dd>
                <dt>narrower</dt>
                <dd>FHIR element is more specific / more constrained than EHDS element.</dd>
                <dt>relatedto</dt>
                <dd>Requires interpretation or transformation; not a direct 1:1 field match.</dd>
                <dt>unmatched</dt>
                <dd>No corresponding element in this profile.</dd>
            </dl>
        </div>
        <div class="table-wrap">
            <table summary="EHDSPatient">
                <caption>EHDSPatient → PatientEuCore</caption>
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th colspan="2" class="src-head">EHDSPatient (Logical Model)</th>
                        <th class="relhead">Relationship</th>
                        <th colspan="3" class="tgt-head">PatientEuCore</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th class="src-sub">Element</th>
                        <th class="src-sub">Description</th>
                        <th class="relsub">Relation</th>
                        <th class="tgt-sub">Element</th>
                        <th class="tgt-sub">Description</th>
                        <th class="tgt-sub">Notes</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td>personalIdentifier</td>
                        <td>
              An identifier of the patient that is unique within a defined scope
              (typically a national patient identifier, but may also be a temporary identifier issued by the EHR).
                        </td>
                        <td>equal</td>
                        <td>identifier</td>
                        <td>Patient identifiers</td>
                        <td></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>name</td>
                        <td>Name associated with the patient / subject.</td>
                        <td>equal</td>
                        <td>name</td>
                        <td>A name associated with the patient</td>
                        <td>See EHDSHumanName → HumanName mapping for sub-elements.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>dateOfBirth</td>
                        <td>Date of birth</td>
                        <td>equal</td>
                        <td>birthDate</td>
                        <td>The date of birth for the patient</td>
                        <td></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>administrativeGender</td>
                        <td>Administrative gender</td>
                        <td>equal</td>
                        <td>gender</td>
                        <td>Administrative gender</td>
                        <td>Binding / allowed values may be constrained by the profile.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>address</td>
                        <td>Mailing and home or office addresses.</td>
                        <td>equal</td>
                        <td>address</td>
                        <td>An address for the individual</td>
                        <td>
              Uses <code>AddressEu</code> in this IG.  
              R4 vs R5 differences are structural only; semantic intent is unchanged.
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>telecom</td>
                        <td>
              Telecommunication contact information (e.g. phone number, email).
              Multiple telecom entries may be provided.
                        </td>
                        <td>equal</td>
                        <td>telecom</td>
                        <td>A contact detail for the patient</td>
                        <td>
              Maps to FHIR <code>ContactPoint</code> (see EHDSTelecom).  
              R4/R5: both use <code>Patient.telecom</code>; no structural split here.
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>maritalStatus</td>
                        <td>Marital (civil) status of a patient</td>
                        <td>equal</td>
                        <td>maritalStatus</td>
                        <td>Marital (civil) status of a patient</td>
                        <td></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>communicationLanguage</td>
                        <td>
              The language which can be used to communicate with the patient about
              his or her health.
                        </td>
                        <td>equal</td>
                        <td>communication.language</td>
                        <td>Communication language</td>
                        <td>
              May be bound to a EU language value set in this IG.
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>
